results.name: Number of non-isomorphic multiset partitions of weight n whose part-sizes have a common divisor > 1.
comment: Also the number of nonnegative integer matrices up to row and column permutations with sum of elements equal to n and no zero rows or columns, in which the column sums are not relatively prime.
Also the number of non-isomorphic multiset partitions of weight n in which the multiset union of the parts is periodic, where a multiset is periodic if its multiplicities have a common divisor > 1.
The weight of a multiset partition is the sum of sizes of its parts. Weight is generally not the same as number of vertices.
